# Upright unit quad for TextNode / VideoNode
# 1x1, centered at origin, standing in the XY plane, facing +Z.
# Double-sided (front + back faces) so it is visible from both sides
# regardless of culling state.
#
# UV convention: plain v=0 at the BOTTOM. The fragment shaders in this
# project (ar_object.frag / ar_text.frag / ar_video.frag) flip V with
# `1.0 - v_TexCoord.y`, which compensates for Android bitmap row order.
# The mesh therefore uses unflipped UVs — do not pre-flip here or text
# and video will render upside down (double flip).

# Vertices (x, y, z) — width along X, height along Y
v -0.5 -0.5 0.0
v  0.5 -0.5 0.0
v  0.5  0.5 0.0
v -0.5  0.5 0.0

# Texture coordinates (u, v) — v=0 at bottom
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0

# Normals
vn 0.0 0.0 1.0
vn 0.0 0.0 -1.0

# Front face (+Z), counter-clockwise winding viewed from +Z
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1
f 1/1/1 3/3/1 4/4/1

# Back face (-Z), counter-clockwise winding viewed from -Z (mirrored)
f 1/1/2 4/4/2 3/3/2
f 1/1/2 3/3/2 2/2/2
